{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MSZqboT7hgVyehfCBwDzNY","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# COORDINATOR_MODE Contract Spec (Rust)\n2\t\n3\t## 1. Objective\n4\t\n5\tDefine Rust rewrite contract for coordinator mode with stable mode-state precedence and tool-allowlist behavior.\n6\t\n7\t## 2. Current Code Evidence\n8\t\n9\t1. `coordinator/coordinatorMode.ts:37` (mode enable check)\n10\t2. `coordinator/coordinatorMode.ts:66` (env mode switch)\n11\t3. `coordinator/coordinatorMode.ts:71` (mode-switch telemetry)\n12\t4. `utils/systemPrompt.ts:63` (coordinator prompt branch)\n13\t5. `tools.ts:120`, `280-293` (tool filtering by coordinator mode)\n14\t6. `cli/print.ts:4918`, `5123` (resume-mode reconciliation)\n15\t\n16\t## 3. Rust Boundary Mapping\n17\t\n18\t1. `api-types`: mode state enums and mode-switch event schema.\n19\t2. `app-services`: effective mode resolution and reconciliation policy.\n20\t3. `tool-runtime`: mode-driven tool allowlist filtering.\n21\t4. `ui-tui`: mode-aware prompt construction and messaging.\n22\t5. `config`: env var and gate keys.\n23\t\n24\t## 4. Proposed Contracts\n25\t\n26\t```rust\n27\tpub trait ModeCoordinatorService: Send + Sync {\n28\t    fn resolve_effective_mode(&self, input: ModeResolutionInput) -> EffectiveMode;\n29\t    fn reconcile_on_resume(&self, session_mode: Option<SessionMode>) -> ModeReconcileResult;\n30\t}\n31\t```\n32\t\n33\tRequired policy:\n34\t\n35\t1. Explicit precedence rule: resumed-session mode vs env mode.\n36\t2. Tool allowlist output is deterministic and testable.\n37\t3. Mode-switch events emit stable metadata.\n38\t\n39\t## 5. Error Taxonomy\n40\t\n41\t```rust\n42\tpub enum CoordinatorModeError {\n43\t    DisabledByPolicy,\n44\t    InvalidModeTransition,\n45\t    SessionModeMismatch,\n46\t}\n47\t```\n48\t\n49\t## 6. Constants Classification\n50\t\n51\t1. `api-types`: mode names and event keys.\n52\t2. `config`: env var keys (`CLAUDE_CODE_COORDINATOR_MODE`) and gate values.\n53\t3. `core-domain`: mode transition invariants.\n54\t4. `ui-tui`: display-only copy.\n55\t\n56\t## 7. Acceptance Matrix\n57\t\n58\t1. Contract tests: precedence and reconcile logic.\n59\t2. Integration tests: resume path updates mode consistently.\n60\t3. CLI behavior tests: tool visibility and prompt mode branch are correct.\n61\t\n62\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01W5T7riSnQ6Hs4WmL3e6Z9H","session_id":"e9f8098c-603d-4cfe-8b30-43f06752a5e5","uuid":"477c5dde-3b8c-4784-a26e-6bd5add40fb6","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:27:52.101Z"}
