{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018bsKNF4xPJrBCPScSV2HaG","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Implementation Phases\n2\t\n3\t## Guiding Principle\n4\t\n5\tBuild bottom-up from the LLM adapter layer. Each phase produces a working, testable vertical slice.\n6\tNo phase depends on features from a later phase. Each phase has explicit exit criteria.\n7\t\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t## Phase 0: LLM Foundation (llm-compat + api-types)\n11\t\n12\t**Goal:** A working dual-provider LLM client that any Rust code can call with a single trait.\n13\t\n14\t### Tasks\n15\t\n16\t1. **Define Canonical types in `api-types`**\n17\t   - `ContentBlock`, `Message`, `Role`, `ToolDefinition`, `LlmRequest`, `LlmResponse`, `StopReason`, `TokenUsage`\n18\t   - `StreamEvent`, `DeltaBlock` for streaming\n19\t   - No provider-specific types here\n20\t\n21\t2. **Refactor `llm-compat` to triple conversion**\n22\t   - Current: `anthropic_request_to_openai_request()` (direct)\n23\t   - Target: `anthropic_to_canonical()`, `canonical_to_anthropic()`, `openai_to_canonical()`, `canonical_to_openai()`\n24\t   - Keep existing tests passing, add Canonical round-trip tests\n25\t\n26\t3. **Add `LlmClient` trait**\n27\t   - `complete(LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError>`\n28\t   - `stream(LlmRequest) -> Result<Stream<StreamEvent>, LlmError>`\n29\t\n30\t4. **Implement `AnthropicAdapter`**\n31\t   - HTTP client (reqwest) for Messages API\n32\t   - SSE parser for streaming\n33\t   - Error mapping (HTTP status -> `LlmError`)\n34\t\n35\t5. **Implement `OpenAiAdapter`**\n36\t   - HTTP client for Chat Completions API\n37\t   - SSE parser for streaming\n38\t   - Error mapping\n39\t\n40\t6. **Add tool_use conversion**\n41\t   - `ToolDefinition` <-> provider tool schemas\n42\t   - `ContentBlock::ToolUse` / `ToolResult` conversion for both providers\n43\t   - `StopReason::ToolUse` mapping\n44\t\n45\t### Exit Criteria\n46\t\n47\t- `cargo test -p api-types -p llm-compat` passes\n48\t- Both adapters can `complete()` against real API (manual/integration test)\n49\t- Both adapters can `stream()` with correct event sequence\n50\t- Tool use round-trip: request with tools -> tool_use response -> tool_result follow-up\n51\t- No provider types visible from `api-types` public API\n52\t\n53\t### Crates Touched\n54\t\n55\t`api-types` (new), `llm-compat` (refactor + extend), `config` (provider/key config)\n56\t\n57\t---\n58\t\n59\t## Phase 1: Agent Loop (app-services)\n60\t\n61\t**Goal:** A minimal agent that can converse and execute tools in a loop.\n62\t\n63\t### Tasks\n64\t\n65\t1. **Define agent loop in `app-services`**\n66\t   - Accept `LlmClient` + tool registry\n67\t   - Loop: send messages -> check stop_reason -> if tool_use, execute tool -> append result -> repeat\n68\t   - Terminate on `EndTurn` or `MaxTokens`\n69\t\n70\t2. **Define `Tool` trait in `tool-runtime`**\n71\t   - `name() -> &str`\n72\t   - `description() -> &str`\n73\t   - `input_schema() -> serde_json::Value`\n74\t   - `execute(input: serde_json::Value) -> Result<String, ToolError>`\n75\t\n76\t3. **Implement core tools**\n77\t   - `ReadFileTool` — read file contents\n78\t   - `WriteFileTool` — write/create files\n79\t   - `EditFileTool` — search-and-replace edits\n80\t   - `BashTool` — execute shell commands\n81\t   - `GlobTool` — file pattern search\n82\t   - `GrepTool` — content search\n83\t\n84\t4. **System prompt composition**\n85\t   - Inject tool definitions into `LlmRequest.tools`\n86\t   - Configurable system prompt\n87\t\n88\t5. **Conversation state**\n89\t   - Message history management\n90\t   - Token budget tracking via `TokenUsage`\n91\t\n92\t### Exit Criteria\n93\t\n94\t- Agent can hold multi-turn conversation with tool use\n95\t- Agent can read a file, edit it, and verify the edit — end-to-end\n96\t- Works with both Anthropic and OpenAI backends (swap via config)\n97\t- Streaming output displays incrementally\n98\t\n99\t### Crates Touched\n100\t\n101\t`app-services` (new), `tool-runtime` (new), `config` (extend)\n102\t\n103\t---\n104\t\n105\t## Phase 2: CLI Interface (app-cli + ui-tui)\n106\t\n107\t**Goal:** Interactive terminal experience.\n108\t\n109\t### Tasks\n110\t\n111\t1. **CLI entrypoint with `clap`**\n112\t   - `ccode` command with subcommands and flags\n113\t   - `--provider`, `--model`, `--system-prompt` flags\n114\t   - Stdin pipe support for non-interactive use\n115\t\n116\t2. **Terminal rendering**\n117\t   - Markdown rendering for assistant responses\n118\t   - Streaming token display\n119\t   - Tool execution status indicators\n120\t   - Input handling (multi-line, history)\n121\t\n122\t3. **IME support**\n123\t   - Grapheme-cluster-aware editing\n124\t   - CJK display-width cursor positioning\n125\t   - Preedit/commit state separation (per acceptance-spec.md 5.4)\n126\t\n127\t4. **Permission system**\n128\t   - Tool execution approval prompts\n129\t   - Auto-allow / ask / deny modes\n130\t\n131\t### Exit Criteria\n132\t\n133\t- `ccode` launches interactive session\n134\t- Streaming responses render in real-time\n135\t- Chinese/Japanese input works correctly\n136\t- Tool use shows execution and result inline\n137\t- Non-interactive pipe mode works (`echo \"question\" | ccode`)\n138\t\n139\t### Crates Touched\n140\t\n141\t`bins/app-cli` (new), `ui-tui` (new)\n142\t\n143\t---\n144\t\n145\t## Phase 3: State & Memory (state-store + config)\n146\t\n147\t**Goal:** Persistent conversation and project context.\n148\t\n149\t### Tasks\n150\t\n151\t1. **Session persistence**\n152\t   - Save/resume conversation history\n153\t   - Session listing and selection\n154\t\n155\t2. **Project context**\n156\t   - CLAUDE.md / project-level instructions loading\n157\t   - Git context awareness (branch, status, recent commits)\n158\t\n159\t3. **Configuration layering**\n160\t   - Global config (`~/.config/ccode/`)\n161\t   - Project config (`.ccode/`)\n162\t   - Environment variables\n163\t   - CLI flag overrides\n164\t\n165\t### Exit Criteria\n166\t\n167\t- Conversations persist and can be resumed\n168\t- Project instructions automatically loaded\n169\t- Config precedence: CLI > env > project > global\n170\t\n171\t### Crates Touched\n172\t\n173\t`state-store` (new), `config` (extend), `platform` (new)\n174\t\n175\t---\n176\t\n177\t## Phase 4: MCP Integration (mcp-runtime)\n178\t\n179\t**Goal:** Model Context Protocol server support.\n180\t\n181\t### Tasks\n182\t\n183\t1. **MCP client implementation**\n184\t   - stdio and SSE transport\n185\t   - Tool/resource/prompt discovery\n186\t   - Server lifecycle management\n187\t\n188\t2. **MCP tool bridge**\n189\t   - MCP tools register as native tools in `tool-runtime`\n190\t   - Permission/approval integration\n191\t\n192\t3. **Server configuration**\n193\t   - Per-project MCP server config\n194\t   - Built-in vs user servers\n195\t\n196\t### Exit Criteria\n197\t\n198\t- External MCP servers can be launched and their tools used\n199\t- MCP tools appear alongside native tools in agent loop\n200\t- Server crash/timeout handled gracefully\n201\t\n202\t### Crates Touched\n203\t\n204\t`mcp-runtime` (new), `tool-runtime` (extend), `config` (extend)\n205\t\n206\t---\n207\t\n208\t## Phase 5: Advanced Features\n209\t\n210\t**Goal:** Multi-agent, remote, and plugin capabilities.\n211\t\n212\t### Sub-phases (can be parallelized)\n213\t\n214\t#### 5a: Multi-Agent (coordinator mode)\n215\t- `AgentTool` for spawning sub-agents\n216\t- Coordinator mode with fan-out/synthesis\n217\t- Task notification system\n218\t- Per `multi-agent-orchestration-contract.md`\n219\t\n220\t#### 5b: Remote Sessions (bridge mode)\n221\t- Remote session lifecycle\n222\t- OAuth/org-scoped auth\n223\t- Archive semantics\n224\t- Per `bridge-mode-contract.md`\n225\t\n226\t#### 5c: Plugin System (plugin-runtime)\n227\t- Plugin loading and capability model\n228\t- Skill/slash-command registry\n229\t- Per `agent-triggers-contract.md`\n230\t\n231\t### Exit Criteria\n232\t\n233\t- Coordinator can spawn parallel workers and synthesize results\n234\t- Remote sessions create/resume/archive correctly\n235\t- Plugin system loads and executes external skills\n236\t\n237\t### Crates Touched\n238\t\n239\tAll remaining crates from workspace layout\n240\t\n241\t---\n242\t\n243\t## Phase 6: Hardening & Release\n244\t\n245\t**Goal:** Production readiness.\n246\t\n247\t### Tasks\n248\t\n249\t1. **Security review**\n250\t   - Secret scanning\n251\t   - Permission boundary tests\n252\t   - Dependency audit (`cargo audit`, `cargo deny`)\n253\t\n254\t2. **Performance**\n255\t   - Cold startup benchmark\n256\t   - Streaming latency benchmark\n257\t   - Memory profiling\n258\t\n259\t3. **CI/CD**\n260\t   - All quality gates from `acceptance-spec.md` section 7\n261\t   - Release packaging (homebrew, cargo install, binaries)\n262\t\n263\t4. **Documentation**\n264\t   - Crate-level READMEs\n265\t   - Operator runbook\n266\t   - ADR directory\n267\t\n268\t### Exit Criteria\n269\t\n270\t- All acceptance criteria from `acceptance-spec.md` pass\n271\t- All codename contracts have passing test suites\n272\t- Release candidate tagged\n273\t\n274\t### Crates Touched\n275\t\n276\t`xtask` (new), `test-support` (new), all crates (hardening)\n277\t\n278\t---\n279\t\n280\t## Dependency Graph (Phase Order)\n281\t\n282\t```\n283\tPhase 0 (llm-compat)\n284\t    ↓\n285\tPhase 1 (agent loop)\n286\t    ↓\n287\tPhase 2 (CLI)     Phase 3 (state)     ← can parallelize\n288\t    ↓                  ↓\n289\tPhase 4 (MCP)\n290\t    ↓\n291\tPhase 5a/5b/5c    ← can parallelize\n292\t    ↓\n293\tPhase 6 (hardening)\n294\t```\n295\t\n296\t## Priority and Scope Notes\n297\t\n298\t- Phase 0-2 is the **minimum viable agent** — a working CLI that can call LLMs and execute tools.\n299\t- Phase 3 adds **daily-driver quality** — persistence and project awareness.\n300\t- Phase 4-5 adds **parity with reference architecture** — MCP, multi-agent, remote.\n301\t- Phase 6 is **release gating** — must pass before any public distribution.\n302\t\n303\tEach phase is independently shippable for internal testing.\n304\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01W5T7riSnQ6Hs4WmL3e6Z9H","session_id":"e9f8098c-603d-4cfe-8b30-43f06752a5e5","uuid":"902e2a5b-38af-4c29-8911-0f8b8c2c4f89","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:28:21.582Z"}
