{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01RAkqMTXimRUJ9oiuDNv9Rx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019H7M9RkmBAmcUWybqgwB1K","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/codename-mapping.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3331,"cache_read_input_tokens":48607,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3331,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01W5T7riSnQ6Hs4WmL3e6Z9H","session_id":"e9f8098c-603d-4cfe-8b30-43f06752a5e5","uuid":"8f125e0b-1cdb-4b96-908d-184c07fa9b32"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019H7M9RkmBAmcUWybqgwB1K","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Codename-to-Rust Mapping and Design Review\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tThis document maps high-impact feature codenames to the Rust rewrite architecture and reviews whether current planned boundaries are reasonable for enterprise maintainability.\n6\t\n7\tPrimary references come from current code paths and gates in:\n8\t\n9\t1. `main.tsx`, `commands.ts`, `tools.ts`, `query.ts`\n10\t2. `bridge/*`, `services/mcp/*`, `services/teamMemorySync/*`\n11\t3. `commands/ultraplan.tsx`, `utils/processUserInput/*`, `coordinator/*`\n12\t\n13\t## A. Codename Mapping (Confidence Ordered)\n14\t\n15\t| Codename | Evidence (sample) | Rust Crates | Notes |\n16\t|---|---|---|---|\n17\t| KAIROS / KAIROS_BRIEF / KAIROS_CHANNELS | `main.tsx:80`, `main.tsx:2206`, `utils/processUserInput/processSlashCommand.tsx:102`, `services/analytics/metadata.ts:735` | `ui-tui`, `app-services`, `tool-runtime`, `api-types` | Assistant-mode family affecting boot path, prompt composition, slash routing, telemetry tags. |\n18\t| BRIDGE_MODE / CCR Remote Control (`tengu_ccr_bridge`) | `entrypoints/cli.tsx:112`, `bridge/bridgeEnabled.ts:34`, `bridge/createSession.ts:134`, `bridge/createSession.ts:263` | `remote-runtime`, `app-services`, `config`, `api-types` | Remote session lifecycle and OAuth/org-scoped headers, with archive semantics and compat paths. |\n19\t| CHICAGO_MCP (computer-use MCP) | `entrypoints/cli.tsx:86`, `services/mcp/client.ts:241`, `services/mcp/config.ts:641`, `query.ts:1033` | `mcp-runtime`, `tool-runtime`, `platform`, `config` | Native-capability MCP path with reserved-name policy and turn-end cleanup hooks. |\n20\t| TEAMMEM (team memory sync) | `setup.ts:365`, `services/teamMemorySync/watcher.ts:253`, `services/teamMemorySync/index.ts:177`, `services/teamMemorySync/index.ts:742` | `state-store`, `remote-runtime`, `config`, `platform` | Bi-directional sync touching OAuth/network + filesystem writes + secret scanning. |\n21\t| AGENT_TRIGGERS / AGENT_TRIGGERS_REMOTE | `tools.ts:29`, `tools.ts:36`, `skills/bundled/index.ts:56`, `tools/RemoteTriggerTool/RemoteTriggerTool.ts:59` | `tool-runtime`, `remote-runtime`, `state-store`, `config` | Local durable cron and remote-trigger API paths with separate gates. |\n22\t| ULTRAPLAN | `commands.ts:104`, `utils/processUserInput/processUserInput.ts:468`, `commands/ultraplan.tsx:330`, `commands/ultraplan.tsx:395` | `ui-tui`, `app-services`, `remote-runtime`, `config` | Keyword/command launch path into long-lived remote session + archive cleanup. |\n23\t| COORDINATOR_MODE | `utils/systemPrompt.ts:63`, `coordinator/coordinatorMode.ts:37`, `coordinator/coordinatorMode.ts:66`, `tools.ts:120` | `app-services`, `tool-runtime`, `ui-tui`, `config` | Mode switch and system-prompt/tool-visibility branch driven by env + gate behavior. |\n24\t| LLM_COMPAT | `crates/llm-compat/src/request.rs`, `crates/llm-compat/src/response.rs`, `crates/llm-compat/src/convert.rs`, `crates/llm-compat/tests/conversion.rs` | `api-types`, `llm-compat`, `config` | Provider-agnostic LLM adapter. Canonical types in `api-types`, triple conversion (Anthropic ↔ Canonical ↔ OpenAI), HTTP client trait, streaming, tool_use mapping. Foundation crate for dual-API agent. |\n25\t\n26\t## B. Service Boundary Fit Review (Is Current Cut Reasonable?)\n27\t\n28\t### 1) BRIDGE_MODE / CCR\n29\t\n30\tVerdict: **Reasonable with one adjustment**.\n31\t\n32\tWhy current cut works:\n33\t\n34\t1. Session lifecycle belongs to `remote-runtime`.\n35\t2. Command entry and UX messaging belong to `ui-tui`/`app-cli`.\n36\t3. Shared session contracts belong to `api-types`.\n37\t\n38\tRequired adjustment:\n39\t\n40\t1. Introduce explicit `RemoteSessionPolicy` in `app-services` for fail-open/fail-close behavior, archive-on-exit guarantees, and resume semantics.  \n41\tWithout this, policy drifts into runtime adapters.\n42\t\n43\t### 2) AGENT_TRIGGERS(_REMOTE)\n44\t\n45\tVerdict: **Mostly reasonable**.\n46\t\n47\tWhy current cut works:\n48\t\n49\t1. Scheduling and tool registration naturally fit `tool-runtime`.\n50\t2. Durable local task persistence fits `state-store`.\n51\t3. Remote trigger dispatch/auth belongs in `remote-runtime`.\n52\t\n53\tRisk:\n54\t\n55\t1. Cron parsing and storage are easy to over-centralize. Keep scheduler core in `tool-runtime`, disk format adapter in `state-store`.\n56\t\n57\t### 3) CHICAGO_MCP\n58\t\n59\tVerdict: **Reasonable but needs strict isolation**.\n60\t\n61\tWhy current cut works:\n62\t\n63\t1. MCP transport/protocol concerns fit `mcp-runtime`.\n64\t2. Tool invocation lifecycle integrates with `tool-runtime`.\n65\t3. Native wrapper/process controls fit `platform`.\n66\t\n67\tRisk:\n68\t\n69\t1. High-privilege local actions can leak into general MCP code.  \n70\tMitigate by splitting `mcp-runtime` into protocol core + computer-use adapter module with explicit capability checks.\n71\t\n72\t### 4) TEAMMEM\n73\t\n74\tVerdict: **Reasonable with contract hardening**.\n75\t\n76\tWhy current cut works:\n77\t\n78\t1. Sync state + merge/persistence belongs to `state-store`.\n79\t2. Network sync endpoints and token auth fit `remote-runtime`.\n80\t3. Path validation and secure write wrappers fit `platform`.\n81\t\n82\tRisk:\n83\t\n84\t1. Secret scanning and path validation can be bypassed if write APIs are inconsistent.  \n85\tMitigate by exposing only one `ValidatedTeamMemWriter` facade from `state-store`.\n86\t\n87\t### 5) ULTRAPLAN\n88\t\n89\tVerdict: **Reasonable**.\n90\t\n91\tWhy current cut works:\n92\t\n93\t1. Keyword/command routing is UI concern.\n94\t2. Remote launch/poll/archive lifecycle is remote concern.\n95\t3. Plan-mode approval policy belongs to `app-services`.\n96\t\n97\tRisk:\n98\t\n99\t1. Orphan session cleanup logic duplicated across UI and remote modules.  \n100\tMitigate with single `UltraplanSessionManager` service interface.\n101\t\n102\t### 6) KAIROS\n103\t\n104\tVerdict: **Reasonable but broad**.\n105\t\n106\tWhy current cut works:\n107\t\n108\t1. Prompt composition and routing span UI + services + tools.\n109\t2. Telemetry marker and capability shaping require shared contracts.\n110\t\n111\tRisk:\n112\t\n113\t1. KAIROS becomes a cross-cutting \"god mode\".  \n114\tMitigate by decomposing into:\n115\t1. `assistant-activation` policy (`app-services`)\n116\t2. `assistant-prompt` composer (`ui-tui`)\n117\t3. `assistant-analytics` emitter (`app-services` with `api-types` tags)\n118\t\n119\t### 7) COORDINATOR_MODE\n120\t\n121\tVerdict: **Reasonable**.\n122\t\n123\tWhy current cut works:\n124\t\n125\t1. Mode state and behavior policy fit `app-services`.\n126\t2. Tool visibility filtering belongs to `tool-runtime`.\n127\t3. Prompt branch in UI/prompt composer remains in `ui-tui`.\n128\t\n129\tRisk:\n130\t\n131\t1. Env-variable mode source can conflict with persisted session mode.  \n132\tMitigate using one `ModeStateStore` contract with deterministic precedence.\n133\t\n134\t### 8) LLM_COMPAT\n135\t\n136\tVerdict: **Reasonable and already partially implemented**.\n137\t\n138\tWhy current cut works:\n139\t\n140\t1. Canonical types naturally belong in `api-types` (shared across all crates).\n141\t2. Provider-specific wire formats and HTTP transport are isolated in `llm-compat`.\n142\t3. `config` controls provider selection and credentials.\n143\t\n144\tRisk:\n145\t\n146\t1. Provider-specific quirks (e.g. OpenAI function_call vs tool_calls, Anthropic thinking blocks) may require adapter-level workarounds that bloat `llm-compat`.\n147\tMitigate by keeping conversion functions per-provider in submodules (`providers/anthropic.rs`, `providers/openai.rs`).\n148\t\n149\t## C. Recommended Interface Contracts (Must Have)\n150\t\n151\tDefine these early in `api-types` + `app-services` traits:\n152\t\n153\t1. `RemoteSessionService`  \n154\tCreate, fetch, archive, resume, poll; explicit result states and timeout taxonomy.\n155\t\n156\t2. `TriggerSchedulerService`  \n157\tCreate/list/delete task; durable vs session-only semantics; ownership checks.\n158\t\n159\t3. `McpCapabilityService`  \n160\tServer registration policy, reserved-name policy, high-privilege capability gates.\n161\t\n162\t4. `TeamMemorySyncService`  \n163\tPull/push/sync with conflict model, secret-scan outcome, path-validation outcome.\n164\t\n165\t5. `ModeCoordinatorService`  \n166\tResolve effective mode from env/session/runtime inputs and expose immutable snapshot.\n167\t\n168\t6. `UltraplanService`  \n169\tLaunch/poll/stop/archive with orphan prevention semantics and idempotent cleanup.\n170\t\n171\t7. `LlmClient` (trait in `llm-compat`)  \n172\t`complete()` and `stream()` operating on Canonical types. Provider adapters implement this trait. Agent loop in `app-services` depends on this trait only.\n173\t\n174\t## D. Constants Classification for These Codenames\n175\t\n176\tApply constants policy from `README.md` with codename examples:\n177\t\n178\t1. `api-types`  \n179\tEvent names: ultraplan lifecycle events, bridge session states, trigger result states.\n180\t\n181\t2. `config`  \n182\tGate keys (`tengu_*`), timeout defaults, retry limits, env var names.\n183\t\n184\t3. `core-domain`  \n185\tInvariants like allowed state transitions (`running -> archived`, not `archived -> running`).\n186\t\n187\t4. Runtime-local crates  \n188\tTransport headers composition details, cache key internals, lock file names.\n189\t\n190\t5. `ui-tui`  \n191\tPrompt/usage text and display-only labels.\n192\t\n193\t## E. Design Validity Conclusion\n194\t\n195\tCurrent rewrite architecture is **structurally valid** for these codenames, but production-grade success depends on three boundary guardrails:\n196\t\n197\t1. Policy interfaces live in `app-services`; runtimes should implement, not define, policy.\n198\t2. High-risk paths (remote session, remote trigger, computer-use MCP, team sync writes) must expose one canonical facade each.\n199\t3. Constants must remain classified by semantics, never by convenience.\n200\t\n201\tWithout those guardrails, the workspace will compile but degrade into cross-crate coupling similar to the current monolith.\n202\t\n203\t## F. Next Deep-Dive Order (Security and Operability First)\n204\t\n205\t1. BRIDGE_MODE / CCR\n206\t2. AGENT_TRIGGERS_REMOTE\n207\t3. CHICAGO_MCP\n208\t4. TEAMMEM\n209\t5. ULTRAPLAN\n210\t6. KAIROS\n211\t7. COORDINATOR_MODE\n212\t8. LLM_COMPAT (foundation — implement first despite lowest risk, as all other codenames depend on it)\n213\t\n214\tThis order matches risk concentration: remote execution and auth boundaries first, broad behavior/prompt orchestration later.\n215\tException: LLM_COMPAT has lowest security risk but highest dependency — it is the foundation crate that all upper layers consume.\n216\t\n217\t## G. Implemented Deep-Dive Specs\n218\t\n219\t1. BRIDGE_MODE / CCR: `docs/bridge-mode-contract.md`\n220\t2. AGENT_TRIGGERS: `docs/agent-triggers-contract.md`\n221\t3. CHICAGO_MCP: `docs/chicago-mcp-contract.md`\n222\t4. TEAMMEM: `docs/teammem-contract.md`\n223\t5. ULTRAPLAN: `docs/ultraplan-contract.md`\n224\t6. Cross-codename integration: `docs/integration-contracts.md`\n225\t7. LLM_COMPAT: `docs/llm-compat-contract.md`\n226\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01W5T7riSnQ6Hs4WmL3e6Z9H","session_id":"e9f8098c-603d-4cfe-8b30-43f06752a5e5","uuid":"824ff5f2-0ef4-4b85-89b3-75e949b97557","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:28:23.531Z"}
