{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W5T7riSnQ6Hs4WmL3e6Z9H","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary report.\n\n## Summary Report: Coordinator Mode Contract & Acceptance Testing Patterns\n\nI've thoroughly explored the project and gathered comprehensive information about the coordinator mode contract and existing acceptance test patterns. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. COORDINATOR MODE CONTRACT (`docs/coordinator-mode-contract.md`)\n\n**File Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/coordinator-mode-contract.md`\n\n**Key Contract Points:**\n- **Objective:** Define Rust rewrite contract for coordinator mode with stable mode-state precedence and tool-allowlist behavior\n- **Error Taxonomy:**\n  - `DisabledByPolicy`\n  - `InvalidModeTransition`\n  - `SessionModeMismatch`\n- **Proposed Trait (spec_contracts.rs:504):**\n  ```rust\n  pub trait ModeCoordinatorService: Send + Sync {\n      fn resolve_effective_mode(&self, input: ModeResolutionInput) -> EffectiveMode;\n      fn reconcile_on_resume(&self, session_mode: Option<SessionMode>) -> ModeReconcileResult;\n  }\n  ```\n- **Boundary Mapping:**\n  - `api-types`: mode state enums and mode-switch event schema\n  - `app-services`: effective mode resolution and reconciliation policy\n  - `tool-runtime`: mode-driven tool allowlist filtering\n  - `ui-tui`: mode-aware prompt construction\n  - `config`: env var (`CLAUDE_CODE_COORDINATOR_MODE`) and gate keys\n- **Acceptance Matrix:**\n  - Contract tests: precedence and reconcile logic\n  - Integration tests: resume path mode consistency\n  - CLI behavior tests: tool visibility and prompt branching\n\n---\n\n### 2. IMPLEMENTATION REFERENCE (`mode_coordinator_service.rs`)\n\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/mode_coordinator_service.rs`\n\n**Key Structures:**\n- `DefaultModeCoordinatorService`: Full implementation of `ModeCoordinatorService`\n- `resolve_effective_mode()`: Implements precedence: session_mode > env_mode > default (Standard)\n- `reconcile_on_resume()`: Handles resume path with conflict detection\n- **Transition Policy:** Coordinator mode is sticky (prevents `Coordinator -> Standard`)\n\n**Included Unit Tests (161-292):**\n- `resolve_effective_mode_prefers_session_over_env_mode`\n- `reconcile_on_resume_uses_session_mode_and_marks_conflict_deterministically`\n- `resolve_effective_mode_reports_disabled_by_policy`\n- `resolve_effective_mode_reports_invalid_transition`\n- `reconcile_on_resume_can_surface_each_error_variant`\n\n---\n\n### 3. RELATED TYPE DEFINITIONS (`spec_contracts.rs`)\n\n**Lines 390-510** contain:\n- `CoordinatorMode` (enum: Standard, Coordinator) with parse method\n- `EffectiveModeSource` (enum: Default, Env, Session)\n- `SessionMode` (struct: mode field)\n- `ModeSwitchReason` (enum: SessionPrecedence, EnvConfigured, DefaultFallback, ResumeReconcile)\n- `ModeSwitchEvent` (from, to, reason)\n- `EffectiveMode` (mode, source, switch_event, error)\n- `ModeReconcileAction` (enum: Noop, SessionWins, EnvAdopted)\n- `ModeReconcileResult` (mode, action, switch_event, error)\n- `CoordinatorModeError` (3 variants as above)\n\n---\n\n### 4. EXISTING ACCEPTANCE TEST PATTERNS\n\n**Two exemplar acceptance test files demonstrate the pattern:**\n\n#### A. Bridge Mode Acceptance Tests (US-037)\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/bridge_mode_acceptance_tests.rs`\n\n**Pattern Structure:**\n```\n1. Shared test doubles (MockCcrClient with fluent builders)\n2. Contract tests (§8.1) — policy/invariant tests\n   - contract_archive_409_is_success_equivalent\n   - contract_session_id_is_preserved_opaquely_by_service\n   - contract_missing_token_produces_auth_unavailable\n3. Integration tests (§8.2) — multi-step lifecycle flows\n   - integration_create_fetch_archive_happy_path\n   - integration_resume_with_expired_session_returns_deterministic_error\n   - integration_shutdown_best_effort_archive_under_timeout_budget\n4. CLI behaviour tests (referenced as separate in crates/cli/src/cmd/bridge.rs)\n```\n\n**Key Pattern Elements:**\n- Mock objects use `Arc<Mutex<VecDeque<Result<...>>>>` for queued results\n- Fluent builder methods: `with_create()`, `with_get()`, `for_happy_path()`\n- Test names follow pattern: `{section}_{scenario}_{assertion}`\n- Comments explain AC (Acceptance Criteria) with markdown anchors to spec doc\n- Each test is focused on ONE contract invariant or integration step\n\n#### B. Chicago MCP Acceptance Tests (US-038)\n**Location:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/mcp-runtime/src/chicago_mcp_acceptance_tests.rs`\n\n**Pattern Structure:**\n```\n1. Shared test doubles (MockLifecycle with atomic counters)\n2. Contract tests (§8.1)\n   - contract_reserved_names_rejected_with_reserved_server_name\n   - contract_privileged_capability_denied_without_feature_gate\n   - contract_cleanup_api_called_for_normal_exit\n3. Integration tests (§8.2)\n   - integration_registration_and_dispatch_happy_path\n   - integration_interrupt_triggers_cleanup_once\n   - integration_cleanup_exception_does_not_poison_subsequent_turns\n```\n\n**Key Pattern Elements:**\n- Comments cite contract file sections: `chicago-mcp-contract.md §8`\n- Atomic counters track lifecycle call sequences\n- Companion tests verify \"also handles X\" scenarios\n- Error cases validated with `expect_err()` + pattern matching\n- Async tests use `#[tokio::test]`\n\n---\n\n### 5. PROJECT ARCHITECTURE CONTEXT\n\n**Crate Structure:** `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/`\n```\napplication/  ← coordinator mode logic lives here\nbootstrap/\ncli/\nconfig/\ncron/\ndomain/\nmcp-runtime/  ← pattern reference (chicago tests)\nplatform/\nports/\nprovider/\nremote-runtime/\nsession/\nstate-store/\ntools/\n```\n\n**Application Crate Contents:**\n- `spec_contracts.rs` - Contract types (14.6K)\n- `mode_coordinator_service.rs` - Implementation (9.8K)\n- `bridge_mode_acceptance_tests.rs` - Test pattern reference (12.2K)\n- `assistant_mode_service.rs`, `remote_session_service.rs`, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 6. US STORY MAPPING\n\nBased on `spec-iterations.md` and `implementation-phases.md`:\n\n- **US-036:** Not explicitly listed; likely coordinator mode unit/contract tests\n- **US-037:** `BRIDGE_MODE / CCR` — Remote session lifecycle (bridge-mode-contract.md)\n- **US-038:** `CHICAGO_MCP` — Computer-use MCP isolation (chicago-mcp-contract.md)\n\nCoordinator mode tests would follow the pattern established by US-037 and US-038.\n\n---\n\n### 7. ACCEPTANCE TEST PLAYBOOK\n\nFrom `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/acceptance-playbook.md`:\n\n**Spec QA Checklist for each contract:**\n1. At least 6 code evidence anchors with file references ✓\n2. Crate boundary section (explicit) ✓\n3. Service trait section with signatures ✓\n4. Error taxonomy section ✓\n5. Constants classification ✓\n6. Acceptance test matrix: contract + integration + CLI tests ✓\n7. IME scenarios (if user input involved) N/A\n\n**Acceptance Test Matrix Template:**\n1. **Entry conditions:** Feature gate, auth/entitlement, config constraints\n2. **State model:** Valid states, transitions, terminal states\n3. **Side effects:** Network, local writes, cleanup\n4. **Error classes:** Policy, transport, data/validation errors\n5. **Observability:** Events, metrics, correlation IDs\n6. **Security controls:** Permission checks, secret/path validation\n7. **Acceptance tests:** Contract + integration + CLI behavior\n\n---\n\n### 8. COMPLETE COORDINATOR MODE TYPE DEFINITIONS\n\n**From `spec_contracts.rs` (lines 401-510):**\n\n```rust\npub const CLAUDE_CODE_COORDINATOR_MODE: &str = \"CLAUDE_CODE_COORDINATOR_MODE\";\n\npub struct ModeResolutionInput {\n    pub policy_enabled: bool,\n    pub env_mode: Option<CoordinatorMode>,\n    pub session_mode: Option<SessionMode>,\n    pub previous_mode: Option<CoordinatorMode>,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\npub enum CoordinatorMode {\n    Standard,\n    Coordinator,\n}\n// parse() method: accepts \"standard\", \"off\", \"false\", \"disabled\" or \n//                           \"coordinator\", \"on\", \"true\", \"enabled\"\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\npub enum EffectiveModeSource {\n    Default,\n    Env,\n    Session,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\npub struct SessionMode {\n    pub mode: CoordinatorMode,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\npub enum ModeSwitchReason {\n    SessionPrecedence,\n    EnvConfigured,\n    DefaultFallback,\n    ResumeReconcile,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\npub struct ModeSwitchEvent {\n    pub from: CoordinatorMode,\n    pub to: CoordinatorMode,\n    pub reason: ModeSwitchReason,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\npub struct EffectiveMode {\n    pub mode: CoordinatorMode,\n    pub source: EffectiveModeSource,\n    pub switch_event: Option<ModeSwitchEvent>,\n    pub error: Option<CoordinatorModeError>,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\npub enum ModeReconcileAction {\n    Noop,\n    SessionWins,\n    EnvAdopted,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\npub struct ModeReconcileResult {\n    pub mode: CoordinatorMode,\n    pub action: ModeReconcileAction,\n    pub switch_event: Option<ModeSwitchEvent>,\n    pub error: Option<CoordinatorModeError>,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, thiserror::Error)]\npub enum CoordinatorModeError {\n    #[error(\"disabled by policy\")]\n    DisabledByPolicy,\n    #[error(\"invalid mode transition\")]\n    InvalidModeTransition,\n    #[error(\"session mode mismatch\")]\n    SessionModeMismatch,\n}\n\npub trait ModeCoordinatorService: Send + Sync {\n    fn resolve_effective_mode(&self, input: ModeResolutionInput) -> EffectiveMode;\n    fn reconcile_on_resume(&self, session_mode: Option<SessionMode>) -> ModeReconcileResult;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Insights for Acceptance Testing\n\n1. **Test Organization:** Contract tests (invariants) separate from integration tests (multi-step flows)\n2. **Mock Doubles:** Use queued result pattern with Arc<Mutex<VecDeque<>>>\n3. **Naming:** Tests are named `{section}_{scenario}_{assertion}`\n4. **Documentation:** Every test has doc comment explaining which AC it covers\n5. **Async Support:** Use `#[tokio::test]` for async tests\n6. **Companion Tests:** Include both success and error paths\n7. **No Poisoning:** Verify that errors don't corrupt state for next operations\n8. **Determinism:** Error classifications must be specific, not generic fallbacks\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive overview should give you a solid foundation for understanding the coordinator mode contract and the expected pattern for acceptance tests!"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e9f8098c-603d-4cfe-8b30-43f06752a5e5","uuid":"0b5cc0d7-48cb-44f3-ba2a-b5f5c55517b5","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:29:07.986Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the coordinator mode contract and existing acceptance test patterns in this Rust project.\n\n1. Find and read the coordinator-mode-contract.md file\n2. Find existing acceptance test files, especially for US-036, US-037, US-038 which are recent test suites\n3. Look at the project structure under crates/ to understand the module layout\n4. Find any existing coordinator mode related code (mode switching, mode precedence, session mode, etc.)\n5. Look for error types like InvalidModeTransition, SessionModeMismatch\n\nBe thorough - read the contract file fully and at least one complete acceptance test file for pattern reference.","agentId":"a6932158d8e46e1f4","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary report.\n\n## Summary Report: Coordinator Mode Contract & Acceptance Testing Patterns\n\nI've thoroughly explored the project 